AN EXPEDITED PACKAGE TO THE UNITED KINGDOM WAS INSPECTED. THERMAL TRACKING LABEL DESCRIBES THE CONTENTS AS A REFURBISHED SCOOTER. INSPECTION OF THE CONTENTS REVEALED ONE ROADRUNNER PRO ELECTRIC SCOOTER WITH A RECHARGEABLE LITHIUM ION BATTERY CONTAINED IN THE SCOOTER. THERE ARE NO DANGEROUS GOODS MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTER BOX. THERE IS NO CUSTOMS INVOICE WITH THE SHIPMENT. THIS PACKAGE HAS NOT BEEN ACCEPTED FOR AIR OR TRANSPORTED IN THE AIR BY UNITED PARCEL SERVICE CO. THIS PACKAGE WAS SHIPPED FROM CALIFORNIA USING UPS ACCOUNT NUMBER 77R96A, VORO MOTORS, INC., 14350 ARMINTA ST, PANORAMA CITY CA 91402-6869.

column169: Dayton Freight observed approximately one (1) gallon of material released from one (1) 5-gallon metal pail due to a forklift puncture. The released material impacted the trailer floor. Dayton Freight personnel cleaned the impacted area with granular absorbents. The spent absorbents were gathered, and the recovered material and damaged pail was containerized into one (1) 55-gallon poly drum. The generated waste was staged onsite at the terminal in a secure location. The generated waste will remain onsite for Dayton Freight’s contracted hazardous waste vendor to coordinate disposal.

column169: It has been brought to our attention that a package was found to be leaking at the unload side. As a precautionary measure, the package was immediately placed in a hazardous bag and subsequently transferred to a red tote. Upon examination, it was discovered that the content had a loose cap, leading to a leakage that spread across the other bottles
